snippet: More than 60,000 country music fans gathered on Saturday at the University of Oklahoma in Norman to watch a concert and help raise money for tornado relief.
abstract: Country singer Toby Keith organizes and headlines concert at University of Oklahoma to raise money for tornado relief; more than 60,000 fans attend sold-out show.
lead_paragraph: More than 60,000 country music fans gathered on Saturday at the University of Oklahoma in Norman to watch a concert and help raise money for tornado relief.

headline.print_headline: A Country Concert For Tornado Victims
headline.main: A Country Concert for Tornado Victims
